    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of dagger or sword popular throughout the Ottoman Empire distinguished by a single-edged blade that curves slightly inward and by a hilt with no guard and two flared wings at the pommel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
